                    <msContents>
                        <summary> <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_2149">Shāhnāmah</title>
                            (Book of Kings), by <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Abū al-Qāsim
                                Manṣūr Firdawsī (fl. ca. 940–1020)</persName>. It opens with a
                            shortened redaction of the Baysunghur preface, followed by the poem
                            proper, of which Abū Manṣūr Daqīqī (d. ca. 980) commenced a thousand
                            lines, but after his death, Firdawsī completed the work shortly before
                            the year <date calendar="#Gregorian" when="1000">1000 CE</date>. He drew
                            upon a number of pre-Islamic Pahlavi middle Persian sources, principally
                            the now-lost <title>Khwadāynāmag</title> (Book of Lords) that recounted
                            the ancient rulers of Persian until the Sassanian period, as well as
                            Iranian mythology and folklore. Previously held in Chetham's Library, Manchester.</summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_1011-item1">
